Done! I've created the React components for device/printer management in `web/dashboard/src/features/devices/`:

**Files Created:**
| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `types.ts` | TypeScript interfaces for Device, Printer, Agent types |
| `api.ts` | API layer using fetch to registry-service endpoints |
| `Devices.tsx` | Main listing page with table/grid view, filtering, and stats |
| `DeviceCard.tsx` | Individual device card with status indicator |
| `DeviceRegister.tsx` | Form for registering new printers and agents |
| `DeviceDetail.tsx` | Detailed device view with status and configuration |
| `index.ts` | Barrel exports |

**Features Implemented:**
- Status indicators (online/offline/error) with visual badges
- Last heartbeat display with formatted "time ago" strings
- Device filtering by status and type
- Table and grid view modes
- Printer enable/disable toggle
- Agent and printer registration forms with validation
- Device detail view with activity timeline
- Stats cards showing total/online devices

**API Endpoints Used:**
- `GET /api/agents` - List agents
- `GET /api/printers` - List printers
- `POST /api/agents` - Register agent
- `POST /api/printers` - Register printer
- `PATCH /api/printers/:id/active` - Enable/disable printer
- `DELETE /api/agents/:id` - Delete agent
- `DELETE /api/printers/:id` - Delete printer

Type-check passed with no errors.
